<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,535]" pageId="4" pageNumber="56">FEMALE GENITALIA: Seventh sternite with hind margin slightly concave. First valvulae with dorsal sculpture granulose, not reaching dorsal margin; apicoventral granulose area present. Second valvulae gradually expanded from midlength to near apex, thereafter tapered to acute apex, without teeth. Third valvulae slightly longer than pygofer, without macrosetae.</paragraph>
